    <stitle>CE 200, CE 300 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE - Accelerator Pedal</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Accelerator Pedal</title>
        <para>The accelerator pedal assembly is a self contained assembly attached to the cowl wall reinforcing mounting
            plate. The accelerator assembly is connected by two mounting bolts to the cowl inside plate assembly. Prior
            to removing the mounting bolts the accelerator harness connection must be unplugged.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900973" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900973.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 79. Accelerator Pedal Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. ACCELERATOR PEDAL ASSEMBLY BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ACCELERATOR PEDAL HARNESS CONNECTION</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ACCELERATOR PEDAL</callout1>
                <callout1>4. ACCELERATOR PEDAL ASSEMBLY MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the accelerator harness connection and disconnect (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900973">Figure 79, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the two mounting bolts attaching the accelerator pedal assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900973">Figure 79, Item 3</hotlnk>) to the cowl reinforcing mounting plate.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the accelerator mounting bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the accelerator pedal assembly.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
